(1)
Cleveland Place (Marion Street), east side, north from, but not including Kenmare, to and including Spring Streets, as seen from Lafayette (Elm) Street. Shown on the S.E. corner of Cleveland Place, at Spring Street, is the East River Savings Bank Building. (No. 60-62 Spring St.)
April 19, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, as seen from Kenmare Street, showing a station of the Free Milk Fund for Babies on the north side of Kenmare Street.
March 16, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
